Package mlogic.algos.graph

Implementation of graph algorithms.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BFS
    Executes breadth first search
    ConnectedComponents
    Uses BFS to determine connected components in an undirected graph
    CutNodeFinder
    Uses DFS to identify cut nodes in a graph.
    CycleDetector
    Detects if a graph has a cycle using DFS
    DFS
    Executes depth first search
    DirectedGraph
    Directed graph data structure.
    Edge
    Represents a path between two nodes in an adjacency-list based graph data structure
    FlowEdge
    Edge in a flow network
    FlowNetwork
    Type of undirected graph used to model and optimize flow in a network
    Graph
    Graph data structure, defaults to undirected graph
    KruskalsMinimumSpanningTree
    Identifies a Minimum Spanning Tree (MST) in an edge-weighted graph using Kruskal's algorithm.
    MaxFlow
    Computes maxflow / mincut in a flow network using Karp implementation of the Ford-Fulkerson method.
    PrimsMinimumSpanningTree
    Identifies a Minimum Spanning Tree (MST) in an edge-weighted graph using Prim's algorithm.
    ReversePostOrder
    Identifies the reverse post order of nodes in a directed graph.
    ShortestPath
    Determines shortest path in un-weighted and undirected graphs using various algorithms
    ShortestWeightedPath
    Determines shortest path in edge-weighted graphs using Dijkstra's algorithm
    StronglyConnectedComponents
    Uses Kosaraju-Sharir algorithm to identify the strongly connected components in a directed graph.
    Topological
    Identifies the topological sort order of nodes in a directed graph.
    UndirectedGraph
    Undirected graph data structure
